\title{shinyformtools: Declarative Database-Backed Shiny Forms}
\description{
Build database-backed 'Shiny' form modules from a single declarative schema. A form is described once and the package derives the database schema, the create, read, update and delete operations, the rendering and the 'Shiny' module from that description. Typical uses range from data-entry forms to questionnaires, surveys and feedback or bug-report boxes. Features include soft deletion with an audit log and record restore, additive schema migrations, database-level uniqueness constraints, configurable table views, dynamic and cross-referencing inputs, server-side validation and a rights-table permission model. The 'SQLite', 'MariaDB' and 'DuckDB' databases are supported behind a common interface.
}
